Public Presentation on Greatness of Kim Jong Il Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 8 (KCNA) -- A public presentation on the greatness of Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il was held by the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces at the April 25 House of Culture on Feb. 7 on the occasion of the February holiday.
 Speakers there said that Kim Jong Il has steadily added luster to the history of great comradeship of the Korean revolution with his outstanding political ability, distinguished leadership art and noble virtue and performed immortal exploits in strengthening the revolutionary armed forces and building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 KPA Vice Marshal Jo Myong Rok, director of the KPA General Political Department, made a speech under the title "Respected Comrade Kim Jong Il is the great leader steadily adding luster to the proud history of the Korean revolution which was started and emerged victorious thanks to comradeship". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He pointed out that Kim Jong Il, on the basis of deep insight into the principle and law of the revolutionary struggle and the historical lesson, became the first in history to project comradeship as the revolutionary philosophy, political philosophy, indicating the most correct way of winning victory in the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 KPA Vice Marshal Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, made a speech under the title "Respected Comrade Kim Jong Il is the great master of creation who opened up a new history in building a great prosperous powerful nation."
 He noted that Kim Jong Il unrolled a grandiose plan for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation with his far-sighted wisdom and matchless grit in the most difficult period of the Korean revolution to instill confidence of sure victory and optimism into the Korean people and has encouraged the People's Army to bear the brunt in the advance with his original Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 KPA General Pak Jae Gyong in his speech titled "Respected Comrade Kim Jong Il is the great illustrious commander who has trained the whole army into the armed forces of the O Jung Hup-led 7th Regiment type devotedly defending the headquarters of the revolution" referred to the exploits he has performed by achieving the greatest success in the history of development of the revolutionary armed forces.
 KPA Lieut. General Jon Chang Bok spoke under the title "Respected Comrade Kim Jong Il is the great father who has shown profound loving care for the servicepersons of the KPA to provide them with excellent living conditions". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers called on all the servicepersons to deeply grasp the greatness of Kim Jong Il, firmly trust and follow him only in any adversity and staunchly struggle to build a great prosperous powerful nation and accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche true to the Songun revolutionary leadership of the Workers' Party of Korea.

Songun Politics of DPRK Praised by Foreign Figures 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 8 (KCNA) -- Otete Gaston Mboyo, chairman of the National Committee of the Genuine Lumumbist Patriotic Party of Democratic Congo, made public a statement on Jan. 30 on the occasion of the February holiday.
 He said that leader Kim Jong Il steering the Workers' Party of Korea and the Korean people along the road of victory is an outstanding thinker-theoretician who has developed in depth the Songun idea based on the great Juche idea and provided a guiding principle for the new era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics has opened a bright prospect of Korean reunification and provided a banner of the struggle for achieving global independence, he noted, adding:
 We extend full support to the WPK and the army and people of the DPRK staging the general march of Songun revolution, while giving full play to the advantages of socialism in all fields including politics, economy and culture, true to the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, Latigo Oral, deputy director for Foreign Relations of the Secretariat of the National Movement of Uganda, and Niombi Tembo, chairman of the Kampala City Committee of the National Movement of Uganda, separately released statements on Jan. 30 and Feb. 1 on the occasion of Feb. 16.

Reception Given at Syrian Embassy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 8 (KCNA) -- Muhammad Adib Alhani, charge d'affaires ad interim of Syria here, hosted a reception at the embassy on Tuesday evening on the occasion of leader Kim Jong Il's birthday. 
 Muhammad Adib Alhani said in a speech that the friendly Korean people have made great achievements in economic construction, adding that the Syrian people standing in the same trench with the Korean people in the struggle against the common enemy are greatly encouraged by their firm solidarity with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that many successes were made in the bilateral relations last year, he expressed hope that these relations would develop on good terms in all fields this year, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minister of Foreign Affairs Paek Nam Sun noted that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries provided by President Kim Il Sung and Hafez al�|Assad, the eternal leader of the Syrian people, are growing stronger day by day under the particular care of the top leaders of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will as ever strive to boost the relations with Syria in all fields as intended by Kim Jong Il, he stressed.

National Meeting of Activists of UAWK Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 8 (KCNA) -- A national meeting of activists of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea (UAWK) took place at the People's Palace of Culture on Feb. 7.
 The meeting reviewed the successes and experience gained in the work of the UAWK under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il in the last period and discussed the tasks and ways of consolidating the UAWK organizations and preparing its members as patriotic farmers in the era of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was attended by Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea, officials concerned and officials of UAWK organizations in Pyongyang and provinces, cities and counties as well as activists of the UAWK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its participants first listened to the recorded speech "On the Main Tasks of the Union of Agricultural Working People" made by President Kim Il Sung on Feb. 16, Juche 61 (1972) at the Second Congress of the Union. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then a report was made by Kang Chang Uk, chairman of the C.C., the UAWK.
 The reporter said that the UAWK organizations regarded it as the most important work of the UAWK to closely rally their members around Kim Jong Il and defend the headquarters of the revolution politically and ideologically and with lives in conformity with the mission and duty as a transmission belt and a body for ideological education of the WPK and has bent great efforts on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Another success registered in the work of the UAWK is that it has mobilized all the agricultural workers to implement the WPK's policy of the agricultural revolution and contribute to accelerating the building of the socialist countryside, he said.
 He underlined the need to develop all the organizations of the UAWK into the revolutionary ranks of Songun capable of contributing to the socialist rural construction and the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche, taking the Songun idea and the undying feats of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il as their life and soul and a source of strength. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He urged the organizations to conduct the positive political work and mass movement to carry out the Party's policy of agricultural revolution, upholding the joint editorial for this year which calls for once again mobilizing and concentrating all forces on the farming. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers underlined the need to thoroughly apply the Songun idea of Kim Jong Il to the work of the UAWK, firmly build up it into a revolutionary body in the era of Songun and dynamically conduct the ideological education of agricultural workers and thus glorify the immortal leadership feats of the Party in the building of the UAWK organizations.

S. Korean Authorities' Projected War Exercises under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 8 (KCNA) -- Some days ago, the minister of Defence of south Korea at a regular press conference blustered that it would go ahead as planned with all the exercises scheduled for this year as well as the joint military exercises with the U.S. due in upcoming March, talking about "training" and strong army" at a time when the hard-won north-south military authorities' talks are at hand. 
 Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun Wednesday terms this an anti-national and anti-reunification outburst intended to drive the situation on the Korean Peninsula to the brink of a war in collusion with outsiders and thus bedevil the north-south relations and overturn the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The news analyst goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the joint military exercises the south Korean warmongers had staged in south Korea with the U.S. imperialist aggression troops since the 1970s were without exception preliminary wars and test nuclear wars to invade the DPRK from A to Z in view of their nature, scale and programs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities are threatening to hold the war exercises to invade the north with outsiders this year too, with the inter-Korean military authorities' talks at hand. This is a challenge to the dialogue partner and a mockery of it.
 Dialogue can never go together with war exercises. The south Korean authorities' announcement of their plan to stage those war exercises against the north goes to prove that "dialogue", "reconciliation," "building of military confidence" and "detente" much touted by them are nothing but rhetoric to deceive the public opinion.
 It is an intolerable anti-national and anti-reunification criminal act for them to join the outsiders in their war maneuvers aimed at seriously threatening the destiny of the nation even in the June 15 era of reunification when the idea of "By our nation itself" dominates the movement for independent reunification and the national cooperation has become the trend of the times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities should clarify before the entire nation whether they stand for reconciliation and cooperation or for confrontation and war.

Nationwide Struggle to Defend Peace Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 8 (KCNA) -- The present tense situation on the Korean Peninsula where the danger of a new war is growing as the days go by requires all the Koreans at home and abroad to turn out as one in the struggle to protect peace from war, observes Rodong Sinmun Wednesday in a signed article. 
 It is a very crucial issue related to the destiny of the Korean nation to oppose aggression and war and defend peace, the article says, and goes on:
 The Koreans in the north and the south have been exposed to the constant threat of war of aggression from the U.S. The U.S. imperialists have threatened peace and security and escalated the war crisis on the Korean Peninsula through ceaseless military provocations and escalation of tensions after occupying south Korea by force and reducing it to a dangerous nuclear forward base. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists' criminal moves to realize their hostile ambition to seize the DPRK have assumed dangerous nature all the times but they have become all the more reckless over the nuclear issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush administration is set to settle the nuclear issue by force despite its lip-service to the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean military, too, is actively supporting the U.S. imperialists' adventurous moves for a war of aggression against the north. They are putting spurs to the development and introduction of F-15K fighters, early warning planes, tanks, armored vehicles, large landing craft, submarines and other war equipment, talking about "independent capability to fight a war" and "deterrent to counter the north". It is also a very disturbing development that the military is readjusting and reorganizing its forces' overall operation commanding system. By backing the U.S.-proposed "strategic flexibility" and "PSI" of its forces in south Korea, in particular, the south Korean authorities are hamstringing the efforts to warm up the inter-Korean relations and sparking a dangerous situation that may lead to an armed conflict any moment in and around the peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Neither peace nor the peaceful reunification of Korea is thinkable without a resolute struggle against the moves for aggression and war on the peninsula. Peace can be won only through a sustained nationwide struggle to protect peace from aggression and war.

Prejudice and Discrimination against Chongryon Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 8 (KCNA) -- Ko Tok U, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and director of the Department for Compatriots' Welfare, issued a statement on Feb. 3 to denounce the Japanese judicial authorities' unwarranted ruling over the exemption of the Kumamoto Korean Hall, a facility related to Chongryon, from tax payment.
 Accusing the Fukuoka High Court of its decision on Feb. 2 to cancel the exemption of the Kumamoto Korean Hall from paying taxes, the statement charged: The court disregarded the public nature of the hall, considering the defence of the interests and rights of the Koreans in Japan as something private. This is a discriminatory judgment in gross violation of the International Human Rights Rules and a very dangerous action to foster xenophobia in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans in Japan are those who survived after being forcibly taken to Japan during the Japanese imperialists' colonial rule and their descendents. This inglorious past, therefore, should be settled at an early date and they should be granted a stable legal status. It is illogical to negate the public nature of the activities to protect the interests and rights of the Koreans in Japan despite these hard facts.
 The statement vehemently denounced the recent judgment as an unwarranted one against a fair legal point of view and an action intended to increase prejudice and discrimination against the DPRK and Chongryon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The judgment also goes against the trend of the times and the desire of the peoples of the two countries as it was made just before the start of the DPRK-Japan inter-governmental talks for the normalization of their relations, it said.

Electric Brush for Turbo Generator Developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 8 (KCNA) -- Scientists of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have recently developed a new kind of electric brush for turbo generator. Good are its quality and technical features.
 The brush, made with natural graphite abundant in the country as the principal component, is applicable to all turbine generators with generation power from one million kW to ten million kW. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The maximum abrasion of the brush is 1.12 millimeters in anode and 0.58 millimeter in negative pole per 100 hours, thus extending the period of changing brushes.
 As its error scale of current distribution equality is below 25 percent in anode and below 10 percent in the negative pole at maximum, it not only prevents generators from being damaged by the brush but ensures their safety reliably. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The brush is produced at the Sobaeksu United Corporation. It mass-produces not only brushes for turbine generators with different kinds of power output but also brushes for car motors and electric motors.
